            <person xml:id="pers1511">
               <p>Sarah Ward was baptized in <placeName>Oxhill, Warwickshire</placeName> in <date
                     when="1747-07">July 1747</date>, and married there on <date when="1772-02-26"
                     >Feb. 26, 1772</date> to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1510.xml"/>James
                     Nind</persName> (d. <date when="1822">1822</date>), of <placeName>Ramsbury,
                     Wiltshire</placeName>. The couple lived on a farm called Ramsbury Park, and
                  hosted <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> there (see
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> to
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName>, <date
                     when="1775-10-17">Oct. 17, 1775</date> and <date when="1775-10-28">Oct. 28,
                     1775</date>). <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1510.xml"/>James</persName>
                  was a local preacher and general steward for the Methodist circuit, while Sarah
                  became a frequent correspondent with <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />JW</persName> until her untimely death in <date when="1783">1783</date>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
